.TH LINMON 1 "March 2026" "linmon 0.1.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
linmon \- Linux terminal monitor for CPU and GPU metrics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B linmon
[\fB-i\fR, \fB--interval\fR \fIMILLISECONDS\fR]
.br
.B linmon
\fBdebug\fR
.br
.B linmon
\fBpipe\fR [\fB-s\fR, \fB--samples\fR \fICOUNT\fR] [\fB--device-info\fR]
[\fB-i\fR, \fB--interval\fR \fIMILLISECONDS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B linmon
shows CPU, swap, memory and NVIDIA GPU metrics in a terminal UI.
It also supports one-shot debug output and JSON streaming mode.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B linmon
Start the interactive terminal UI.
.TP
.B linmon debug
Print device info and one metrics sample as JSON.
.TP
.B linmon pipe
Print metrics as JSON. Use \fB-s\fR 0 for continuous output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-interval " " \fIMILLISECONDS\fR
Refresh interval in milliseconds.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-samples " " \fICOUNT\fR
Number of JSON samples in pipe mode. Zero means continuous output.
.TP
.B \-\-device-info
Append device information in pipe mode.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/linmon/config.json
User configuration.
.SH AUTHORS
ailuntz
.SH HOMEPAGE
https://github.com/ailuntz/linmon
